text: Highway 15 (British Columbia Highway 15) is a highway that acts as the border between Surrey and Langley. The northern part of Highway 15 is also known as the Pacific Highway while the southern part of Highway is also known as 176th Street. Its north end is at with a junction with Highway 17 and Highway 1 while the south end is at the Pacific Highway Border Crossing near Blaine. Category:British Columbia provincial highways
title: British Columbia Highway 15
